publish over ssh
=>create a new job
=>manage jenkins=>plugins=>available plugins=>publish over ssh(install)
=>manage jenkins=>system=>configure=>publish over ssh=>ssh server=>add name=>tomcat-server
					hostname->ipadderess of tomcat
					username=>ece-user
				key=>check for password authentication=>paste rsa key of tomcat instance in the key field
navigate back to created job
=>post build actions=>send build artifact over ssh=>in the transfer=>source files:target/helloworld.war
						=>remove prefix=>target
						=>remove directory=>//opt//tomcat//webapps
=>apply and save
before building it =>in the tomcat instance run these two commands=>
$ sudo usermod -aG root ec2-user
$ sudo chmod -R g+w /opt/tomcat/webapps
